<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><div style="margin: 0px;"><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">We are now in the third year of developing our secondary BSY Literary Canon: this is a collection of 20 books chosen by the school community that students, parents and BSY staff are encouraged to read to promote shared conversation around books and build cultural capital.</div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Each year, students, parents and staff nominate and vote for books of their choice to be added&nbsp;to the Canon, and so I am writing to ask for your book nominations. Last year, a number of parents made suggestions, and the parent community voted for Ready Player One and Trash to be added to the collection (both of which I have read this year and thoroughly&nbsp;appreciated). I have attached this year's Canon so that you can see our overall collection so far.&nbsp;</div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Each year, we will replace five texts - two chosen by parents, two by students and one by staff. So please add your suggestions to<a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/110fpOS3LCQjuHpBkdLGrd5YNpPTLL41o7cM_WMYqjYI/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/110fpOS3LCQjuHpBkdLGrd5YNpPTLL41o7cM_WMYqjYI/edit?usp%3Dsharing&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1557192704606000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHHMRN3HimPv2_wlmxmP2M3sq1IFA" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204);">&nbsp;this spreadsheet.</a>&nbsp;When nominating texts, please consider whether it is age appropriate for students aged 11+ and also think about what cultural capital it would bring to the collection - does it explore a&nbsp;different culture? Engage with philosophical or social issues? Is the text structured in an unconventional way, or&nbsp;narrated by someone unexpected?&nbsp;</div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Please add your suggestions by Friday May 10th. If you have any questions, please&nbsp;don't hesitate to contact me.&nbsp;</div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Many thanks,</div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Rebecca</div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><div>&nbsp;</div><div dir="ltr" class="m_-133309611573588668m_-8074556841943442942gmail_signature" data-smartmail="gmail_signature"><div dir="ltr"><div dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-weight: 700; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Rebecca Kearon-Wiles </span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Literacy Coordinator, English Teacher and 7RKW Form Tutor</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div></font></span></div><div style="text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font size="2" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="">The British School Yangon</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" size="2">www.britishschoolyangon.org</font></p></div></div>]]></td>
